    <entry>
      <title>The procedure of C programming in Linux</title>
      <link href="/2024/11/15/The-procedure-of-C-programming-in-Linux/"/>
      <url>/2024/11/15/The-procedure-of-C-programming-in-Linux/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="The-procedure-of-C-programming-in-Linux"><a href="#The-procedure-of-C-programming-in-Linux" class="headerlink" title="The procedure of C programming in Linux"></a>The procedure of C programming in Linux</h1><h2 id="Set-up-essential-environment"><a href="#Set-up-essential-environment" class="headerlink" title="Set up essential environment"></a>Set up essential environment</h2><p>Linux have set up all default. </p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">sudo apt update</span><br><span class="line">sudo apt install build-essential</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>If you Linux didn’t set up well. </p><h2 id="Write"><a href="#Write" class="headerlink" title="Write"></a>Write</h2><ul><li>create a file name <filename>.c. </li><li>write the programme. For example: <figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"># include &lt;stdio.h&gt;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">int main() &#123;</span><br><span class="line">printf(&quot;Hello, world!\n&quot;);</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">return 0;</span><br><span class="line">&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li></ul><h2 id="Complie"><a href="#Complie" class="headerlink" title="Complie"></a>Complie</h2><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">gcc -o &lt;whatever&gt; &lt;filename&gt;.c</span><br><span class="line">./&lt;whatever&gt;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>]]></content>
      
      
      <categories>
          
          <category> C </category>
          
      </categories>
      
      
    </entry>
    
    
    
    <entry>
      <title>Have To Execute Hexo With Sudo</title>
      <link href="/2024/11/15/have-to-execute-hexo-with-sudo/"/>
      <url>/2024/11/15/have-to-execute-hexo-with-sudo/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Have-to-execute-hexo-with-sudo"><a href="#Have-to-execute-hexo-with-sudo" class="headerlink" title="Have to execute hexo with sudo"></a>Have to execute hexo with sudo</h1><h2 id="Reason"><a href="#Reason" class="headerlink" title="Reason"></a>Reason</h2><figure class="highlight plaintext"><figcaption><span>hexo init``` is the reason.</span></figcaption><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">## Solution</span><br><span class="line"></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>sudo chown -R azureuser:azureuser &#x2F;path&#x2F;to&#x2F;hexo&#x2F;folder<br>chmod -R u+rwX &#x2F;path&#x2F;to&#x2F;hexo&#x2F;folder</p><pre><code>- change the /path/to/hexo/folder to that init executed. - remember do not ```sudo hexo init``` again. </code></pre>]]></content>
      
      
      
